    h2 Privacy Policy
    .fine-print
      h4 Our Privacy Commitment
      p
        | PinPigeon, LLC. ("PinPigeon," "we," "us" or "our") is committed to respecting the privacy rights and concerns of all users of  our websites where this Privacy Policy is posted (the "Sites"), the PinPigeon browser extension and other mobile and/or social network apps we distribute (the "Apps" and collectively with the Sites and the services made available through the Apps and the Sites, the "PinPigeon Features").  As such, we have established and implemented this Privacy Policy to inform visitors and users of the PinPigeon Features how we use and protect the information we collect through the Service.  By visiting the Sites or using the PinPigeon Features, you consent to PinPigeon's collection, use, storage, deletion and disclosure of information relating to you as set forth in this Privacy Policy.
      br
      p
        | This Privacy Policy is effective as of the date set forth above and is only applicable to the Apps and the Sites and not to any other website or social network service (including, without limitation, www.facebook.com ("Facebook")) or any other mobile software applications (including, without limitation, the PinPigeon browser extension ("PinPigeon") that you may be able to access from, or interact with, the PinPigeon Features and which websites or applications may have their own data collection and use practices and policies.
      p
        | This policy answers the following questions:
        ul
          li What information do we collect about you and how do we use it?
          li Will we share your personal information with third parties?
          li
            | What choices do you have about the collection and use of your personal information?
          li What security measures do we take to safeguard your personal information?
      h4 What information do we collect about you and how do we use it?
      h5 Types of Information We Collect
      p
        | Personal information means information that can be used to identify and contact you. You do not need to submit personal information to access certain aspects of the PinPigeon Features, but if you do not want to disclose certain personal information to us, you will not be able to use all aspects of the PinPigeon Features.  For example, you will not be able to order photographs through the PinPigeon Features without setting up an account and providing certain personal information.
      p
        | We collect personal information when you log into the PinPigeon Features through your PinPigeon account, create an account through the PinPigeon Features; subscribe to our newsletter; participate in chat rooms, forums, polls, surveys, news groups and questionnaires; participate in contests, sweepstakes, or other promotions; purchase photographs through the PinPigeon Features; or receive customer or technical support.
        | To create an account for the PinPigeon Features, we require you to provide your name, a username, password, mailing address, mobile phone number, home telephone number and email address.  When you are purchasing products through the PinPigeon Features, we will also ask for your credit card or other payment information.
      br
      p
        | Additionally, we may also collect other types of information (known as demographic information) such as your gender, hobbies, occupation, and entertainment preferences information. This demographic information may be associated with your personal information.
        | Should you access the PinPigeon Features through Facebook or integrate the PinPigeon Features with your Facebook profile or PinPigeon account, we will have access to, and collect certain information from that  profile or account.  We collect your PinPigeon username, password, account photo and the email account associated with your PinPigeon account.  We also collect photographs that you submit from PinPigeon to the App.  The information that we access from your Facebook profile is determined through the privacy settings that you have established for your Facebook profile and account.  For example, we may access and store some or all of the following information from your Facebook profile depending on the privacy settings you have selected through your Facebook account:  your name, birthday, gender, user ID number, user ID number of your friends, the email address you use with your Facebook account, your profile picture, and your physical location.
        | We may also collect additional information regarding your hobbies, interests or "likes" that you make available through your Facebook profile and we may group that information with your personal information.
      h4 How We Use Your Personal Information
      p
        | The personal information you provide to us will allow us to alert you of new products or services, features, or enhancements and handle/route your customer service questions or issues; and/or notify you of special events and offers. We also use your e-mail address and mobile phone number to send you messages about the PinPigeon Features and other general announcements.
      br
      p
        | We use the information regarding your hobbies, interests or "likes" that you make available through your Facebook profile for the purpose of suggesting content to you that we believe you will find interesting.
        | We keep track of your interactions with us, including but not limited to your activity within the PinPigeon Features. We may use personal information that you provide to us to send messages to you in response to your request to perform an activity in connection with your use of any of the PinPigeon Features. We may also use your personal information to contact you when necessary.
      h4 Cookies
      p
        | "Cookies" are small bits of electronic information that a website sends to a visitor's browser and are stored on the visitor's hard drive. Like many websites, we employ cookies in certain areas of the PinPigeon Features to allow us to provide information which is targeted to your interests and to make your online experience more convenient. For example, when you return to the PinPigeon Features after logging in through your account username, cookies provide information to the PinPigeon Features so that the PinPigeon Features will remember who you are.  Should you disable cookies in your browser, you will have to provide your account username each time you want to log in.
      h4 Log Information
      p
        | Our servers automatically record information that your browser sends whenever you visit the PinPigeon Features.  This information includes your Internet Protocol address, your browser type and version, the search engine you used to find the PinPigeon Features, if any, the operating system your computer uses, which PinPigeon Features you use and when and how long you use them.  We use this information to monitor and analyze how users use the PinPigeon Features, to provide customer service and to maintain and improve the PinPigeon Features.
      p
        h4 Our Invitation Service
        p
          | If you choose to use our invitation service to tell a friend about the PinPigeon Features, we will ask you for information needed to send the invitation, such as your friend's name and email address.  We will automatically send your friend an email or instant message inviting him or her to visit the Site(s) or download an App.  We may, from time to time, continue to send messages to your friend as a reminder of your invitation.  If your friend has not registered with the Sites or the Apps after we have contacted them on 2 occasions, we will stop sending your friend messages and will delete his or her information.
          | Children's Privacy
          | We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. We take children's privacy seriously, and encourage parents to play an active role in their children's online experience at all times.
        h4
          | Will we share your personal information with third parties?
          h4
            h5 Sharing of Information
            p
              | We may use your personal information to provide analyses of our users in the aggregate to prospective partners, advertisers and other third parties, such as, for example, disclosing how many users of the PinPigeon Features are between the ages of 24 and 32 and how many of those users are male or female.  We may also disclose and otherwise use, on an anonymous basis, the information regarding your hobbies, interests and "likes" and other non-personal information so that we may obtain new content for the PinPigeon Features.
            br
            p
              | In addition, we will share the personal information we collect from you under the following circumstances:
              ul
                li
                  | Protection of rights.  We will share personal information if we have a good faith belief that (i) access, use, preservation or disclosure of such information is reasonably necessary to satisfy any applicable law, regulation, legal process, such as a court order or subpoena, or a request by law enforcement or governmental authorities, (ii) such action is appropriate to enforce the Terms of Use for the PinPigeon Features, including any investigation of potential violations thereof, (iii) such action is necessary to detect, prevent, or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues associated with the PinPigeon Features, or (iv) such action is appropriate to protect the rights, property or safety of PinPigeon, its employees, users of the PinPigeon Features or others.
                li
                  | Asset transfers.  If we become involved in a merger, acquisition or other transaction involving the sale of some or all of PinPigeon' assets, user information, including personal information collected from you through your use of the PinPigeon Features, could be included in the transferred assets.  Should such an event occur, we will use reasonable means to notify you, either through email and/or a prominent notice on the Site(s).
                li
                  | Service Providers.  We may share your personal information with service providers that we engage for the purpose of processing information on our and your behalf.  For example, we have partnered with other companies to host data uploaded through the PinPigeon Features, process payments when you order photographs through the PinPigeon Features and to print those photographs and deliver them to the addresses indicated in your order.  While providing services for us, these companies may access your personal information or the personal information of the individuals that are to receive your photographs.  To the extent applicable, we require these entities to comply with this Privacy Policy and appropriate confidentiality and security measures.
            h4 Additional Information You Should Know About Third Parties
            p
              | This Privacy Policy does not cover the information practices of third party websites linked to the PinPigeon Features. Although we encourage such third parties to adopt and follow their own privacy policies, we are not responsible for their collection and use of your personal information.  This Privacy Policy also does not cover the information practices of the distributors of the Apps.  For example, if you download the Apps through the Apple App Store, you are subject to Apple, Inc.'s privacy policy.  You should refer to the privacy policies and statements of other websites and App distributors or contact the respective webmasters of those websites or administrative contacts of App Distributors to obtain information regarding their information collection, use and disclosure policies.
              | When you have clicked on an advertisement or third party logo displayed on the PinPigeon Features which links you to a different website, our Privacy Policy no longer applies and you must read the privacy policy of the advertiser to see how your personal information will be handled on their website.
              | The PinPigeon Features may also have message boards and forums where users can exchange ideas and communicate with one another.  When you post to a message board or forum, please be aware that the information you post is made publicly available on-line and you do so at your own risk.
            h4
              | What choices do you have about the collection and use of your personal information?
            h5 Control of Your Information
            p
              | You may update or delete your personal information or modify your account preferences for the PinPigeon Features by accessing the "My Account" area of the PinPigeon Features.  Please note that when you delete your account, we may retain your account information for a reasonable period of time afterward for the purpose of internal account management and fraud prevention activities. You may also request that we delete your personal information by sending an email to support@pinpigeon.com.  Please note that when you request to have your personal information deleted, we may retain certain personal information for a reasonable period of time afterward for the purpose of internal account management and fraud prevention activities.
              | Opting Out of Receiving Communications from Us
              | If you no longer want to receive our newsletter, e-mails or other announcements, you may unsubscribe by selecting "unsubscribe" in your account, writing to us at support@pinpigeon.com or replying to the unsubscribe link at the bottom of our e-mails.  Please note that you cannot unsubscribe from certain correspondence from us, including messages relating to your account transactions.
            h4 Mediation
            p
              | If you are a resident of a country outside of the European Union, you also agree that, in the event any dispute or claim arises out of or relating to this Privacy Policy that you and PinPigeon will attempt in good faith to negotiate a written resolution of the matter directly between the parties.  You agree that if the matter remains unresolved for forty-five (45) days after notification (via certified mail or personal delivery) that a dispute exists, all parties shall join in mediation services in Greensburg, Pennsylvania with a mutually agreed mediator in an attempt to resolve the dispute.  Should you file any arbitration claims, or any administrative or legal actions without first having attempted to resolve the matter by mediation, then you agree that you will not be entitled to recover attorney's fees, even if you would otherwise be entitled to them.
            h4 Dispute Resolution for Residents of the European Union
            p
              | If you are a resident of the European Union, in the event that you have any dispute or claim arising out of or relating to this Privacy Policy, you may report your claim to the European Union Data Protection Authorities located in your jurisdiction.
            h4 What security measures do we take to safeguard your personal information?
            p
              | The personal information that you provide to us is stored on servers, which are located in secured facilities with restricted access, and protected by protocols and procedures designed to ensure the security of such information.  In addition, we restrict access to personal information to PinPigeon employees, independent contractors and agents who need to know this information in order to develop, operate and maintain the PinPigeon Features.  All PinPigeon personnel who have access to this information are trained in the maintenance and security of such information.  However, no server, computer or communications network or system, or data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure.  As a result, while we strive to protect user information, we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us or through the use of any of the PinPigeon Features and you acknowledge and agree that you provide such information and engage in such transmissions at your own risk.  Once we receive a transmission from you, we will endeavor to maintain its security on our systems.
            h4 European Commission's Directive on Data Protection - Safe Harbor
            p
              | PinPigeon adheres to the Safe Harbor Principles that were established by the U.S. Department of Commerce in consultation with the European Commission to comply with the European Commission's Directive on Data Protection.
            h4 Notification of Changes
            p
              | This Privacy Policy may change from time to time and we will post all changes on this page.
            h4 Questions?  Contact Us
            p
              | If you have any questions about our privacy practices or this Privacy Policy, please contact us by email at
              | &nbsp;
              a(href='mailto:support@pinpigeon.com') support@pinpigeon.com
            h4 Terms of Service
            p
              | Please read the Terms of Service at pinpigeon.com/tos governing the use of the Site(s) and the PinPigeon Features.
